section.text:

  Section 11(f) of the Endangered Species Act of 1973 (
  16 U.S.C. 1540(f)
) is amended—

clause.text:
prohibit or restrict the possession, sale, delivery, receipt, shipping, or transportation, within
			 the United States, of elephant ivory that has been lawfully imported into
			 the United States;

change any methods of, or standards for, determining if such ivory has been lawfully imported that
			 were in effect on February 24, 2014, including any applicable presumptions
			 and burdens of proof with respect to such determinations;
